label: A Brief Sketch of Historic Charleston
description: Presents "in a condensed form the historic and interesting points of interest in and near Charleston most sought after by tourists and visitors."  Includes "interesting facts about the first churches and congregations; old historic buildings, halls and colleges; historical houses; relics of the old days; queer streets, alleys and lanes; parks, squares, cemeteries."  Map of the peninsula includes "a sketch of the resorts and historical points in and around Charleston."  Cover title:  Guide Book of Historic Charleston and Map.  Published by Lanneau's Art Store (Charleston, S.C.).  24 p., 16 cm. + 1 map, 40 x 50 cm. folded to 10 x 14 cm.  (Note:  paging begins at page 3.)
